    "file": "content/education/alternative_assets/tokenized_assets.md",
    "content": "# Tokenized Assets\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nTokenized assets are traditional assets represented as digital tokens on a blockchain.\n\n### Origin\nInstitutional adoption accelerated after 2022 with regulatory clarity.\n\n### Why It Matters\nTokenization enables fractional ownership and programmable settlement.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nAssets are custodied off-chain while tokens represent claims on-chain.\n\n### How It Behaves\nLiquidity improves for illiquid assets while regulatory risks remain.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Total tokenized market capitalization\n- On-chain transfer volume\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nAsset managers issue tokenized funds to reduce settlement times.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Tokenized money-market funds\n- Fractional real estate\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Liquidity Agent**: Monitors tokenized asset flows.\n- **Portfolio Agent**: Integrates tokenized yield.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nTokenization bridges traditional finance and blockchain infrastructure.\n\n## Related Topics\n- stablecoins.md\n- private_credit.md\n"
