    "content": "# Agent Consensus\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nAgent consensus is the process by which specialized Arkhe agents reach agreement on market signals and actions.\n\n### Origin\nEvolved from distributed AI research scaled with large language models.\n\n### Why It Matters\nConsensus reduces individual agent hallucination and increases decision robustness.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nAgents communicate through shared memory and structured debate protocols.\n\n### How It Behaves\nConsensus is strongest when multiple independent signals align.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Number of agreeing agents\n- Confidence distribution\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nArkhe uses consensus as the final gate before execution or allocation.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- High-conviction trade approval\n- Regime classification\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\nAgent consensus is the core validation layer of the Arkhe swarm.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nAgent consensus is the quality control mechanism of Arkhe intelligence.\n\n## Related Topics\n- swarm_architecture.md\n"
