    "content": "# Arkhe Risk Engine\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nThe Arkhe Risk Engine is the dedicated multi-agent system that monitors, quantifies, and mitigates portfolio risk in real time.\n\n### Origin\nBuilt as a core specialized agent cluster within Arkhe.\n\n### Why It Matters\nRisk-first design is fundamental to Arkhe’s institutional architecture.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nThe engine aggregates signals from all agents to compute VaR, expected shortfall, and drawdown probabilities.\n\n### How It Behaves\nRisk engine overrides can reduce exposure even when other agents are bullish.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Real-time drawdown probability\n- Tail-risk metrics\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nArkhe Risk Engine enforces hard limits and dynamic sizing for all portfolios.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Pre-trade risk validation\n- Live portfolio rebalancing under stress\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Risk Agent**: Core engine for all risk calculations.\n- **Supervisor Agent**: Enforces risk overrides.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nThe Arkhe Risk Engine is the guardian of capital preservation within the swarm.\n\n## Related Topics\n- arkhe_supervisor_agent.md\n"
