    "content": "# Arkhe Signal Scoring\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nArkhe signal scoring is the multi-agent process that assigns probabilistic confidence to market signals.\n\n### Origin\nBuilt as the native scoring layer of the Arkhe swarm.\n\n### Why It Matters\nSignal scoring provides calibrated probabilities rather than binary decisions.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nEach agent contributes a score; swarm aggregates into a final confidence metric.\n\n### How It Behaves\nHigh scores require alignment across multiple specialized agents.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Agent-level confidence\n- Swarm consensus strength\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nArkhe signal scores are used for position sizing and risk budgeting.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Conviction-weighted allocation\n- Dynamic hedging triggers\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\nSignal scoring is the native output format of the Arkhe swarm.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nArkhe signal scoring transforms raw signals into institutionally usable probabilities.\n\n## Related Topics\n- arkhe_risk_engine.md\n"
