    "content": "# Arkhe Supervisor Agent\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nThe Arkhe Supervisor Agent is the oversight layer that validates swarm consensus and enforces institutional rules.\n\n### Origin\nBuilt as the governance layer of the Arkhe swarm.\n\n### Why It Matters\nSupervisor prevents rogue decisions and maintains compliance.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nSupervisor reviews high-stakes decisions and can override or require human escalation.\n\n### How It Behaves\nSupervisor acts as the final quality gate before execution.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Override frequency\n- Rule violation alerts\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nSupervisor Agent mirrors institutional risk committee functions.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Hard limit enforcement\n- Human-in-the-loop escalation\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Supervisor Agent**: Final validation layer for all swarm outputs.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nThe Arkhe Supervisor Agent is the institutional control layer of the swarm.\n\n## Related Topics\n- arkhe_risk_engine.md\n"
