    "file": "content/education/asset_classes/commodities.md",
    "content": "# Commodities\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nCommodities are physical goods traded on futures exchanges that serve as economic inputs.\n\n### Origin\nOrganized futures trading began in the 19th century.\n\n### Why It Matters\nCommodities act as inflation hedges and reflect real economic dynamics.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nFutures contracts enable price discovery and hedging.\n\n### How It Behaves\nCommodities are pro-cyclical and exhibit mean reversion.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Inventory levels\n- Futures curve shape\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nCTAs and producers use futures for tactical overlays.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Inflation-protected portfolios\n- Basis trading\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Macro Agent**: Correlates prices with growth and inflation.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nCommodities are the real-economy counterpart to financial assets.\n\n## Related Topics\n- currencies.md\n- fixed_income.md\n"
