    "file": "content/education/asset_classes/currencies.md",
    "content": "# Currencies\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nCurrencies are fiat money issued by governments that serve as the medium of exchange.\n\n### Origin\nThe modern floating exchange-rate system began in 1971.\n\n### Why It Matters\nCurrency movements drive global capital flows and investment returns.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nCurrencies trade 24 hours with prices driven by interest-rate differentials.\n\n### How It Behaves\nMajor reserve currencies exhibit mean-reverting behavior.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Real effective exchange rates\n- Interest-rate differentials\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nGlobal macro funds manage large currency exposures.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Carry-trade portfolios\n- Currency hedging\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Macro Agent**: Tracks rate differentials and flows.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nCurrencies are the transmission mechanism of global monetary policy.\n\n## Related Topics\n- forex.md\n- reserve_currency.md\n"
