    "file": "content/education/asset_classes/derivatives.md",
    "content": "# Derivatives\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nDerivatives are financial contracts whose value is derived from an underlying asset.\n\n### Origin\nModern derivatives expanded after the 1970s.\n\n### Why It Matters\nDerivatives enable risk transfer and efficient capital allocation.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nCommon types include futures, options, and swaps priced under no-arbitrage assumptions.\n\n### How It Behaves\nDerivatives amplify gains and losses and create feedback loops.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Open interest\n- Implied volatility\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nInstitutions use derivatives for hedging and relative-value trading.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Portfolio insurance\n- Volatility arbitrage\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Execution Agent**: Optimizes derivative hedging.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nDerivatives are the precision tools of professional risk management.\n\n## Related Topics\n- options.md\n- futures.md\n"
