    "file": "content/education/asset_classes/equities.md",
    "content": "# Equities\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nEquities represent ownership shares in companies and entitle holders to residual cash flows.\n\n### Origin\nModern equity markets originated with the Dutch East India Company in 1602.\n\n### Why It Matters\nEquities are the primary vehicle for long-term capital appreciation.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nEquities trade on exchanges with price discovery driven by supply and demand.\n\n### How It Behaves\nEquities exhibit long-term upward drift with periodic drawdowns tied to earnings cycles.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Earnings growth\n- Institutional ownership\n- Buyback and dividend yields\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nInstitutions dominate volume through algorithmic execution and dark pools.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Factor-based equity portfolios\n- Sector rotation strategies\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Technical Agent**: Monitors sector rotation.\n- **Portfolio Agent**: Optimizes equity beta.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nEquities are the foundational growth asset class.\n\n## Related Topics\n- fixed_income.md\n- derivatives.md\n"
