    "route": "/education/institutional/prime_brokerage",
    "file": "content/education/institutional/prime_brokerage.md",
    "content": "# Prime Brokerage\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nPrime brokerage is the bundle of financing, custody, and operational services provided to hedge funds.\n\n### Origin\nThe model expanded in the 1990s with hedge fund growth.\n\n### Why It Matters\nPrime brokers are the operational backbone of institutional trading.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nServices include margin lending, securities lending, and consolidated reporting.\n\n### How It Behaves\nPrime brokers are profitable in normal markets but exposed to funding liquidity risk.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Prime broker balances\n- Securities lending revenue\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nHedge funds use multiple prime brokers to diversify counterparty risk.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Portfolio financing\n- Synthetic prime for digital assets\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Risk Agent**: Monitors prime broker exposure.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nPrime brokerage enables hedge funds to operate efficiently with leverage.\n\n## Related Topics\n- hedge_fund_structure.md\n- clearing_houses.md\n"
