    "title": "Risk Committees",
    "category": "institutional",
    "slug": "risk_committees",
    "route": "/education/institutional/risk_committees",
    "file": "content/education/institutional/risk_committees.md",
    "content": "# Risk Committees\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nRisk committees oversee and approve risk exposures across an institution.\n\n### Origin\nRisk committees became standard after the 2008 crisis.\n\n### Why It Matters\nRisk committees enforce discipline and prevent excessive risk-taking.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nCommittees review VaR, stress tests, and concentration limits.\n\n### How It Behaves\nEffective committees balance business objectives with prudent limits.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Risk limit utilization\n- Stress-test breaches\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nSophisticated firms maintain independent risk committees with direct board reporting.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Pre-approval of new strategies\n- Crisis response planning\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Supervisor Agent**: Aggregates multi-agent risk views.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nRisk committees translate risk policy into operational reality.\n\n## Related Topics\n- risk_management.md\n"
