    "file": "content/education/institutional/sovereign_wealth_funds.md",
    "content": "# Sovereign Wealth Funds\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nSovereign wealth funds are state-owned investment vehicles managing national savings or commodity revenues.\n\n### Origin\nThe first modern funds were established in the 1950s.\n\n### Why It Matters\nSovereign wealth funds are among the largest patient capital pools globally.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nFunds follow mandates ranging from stabilization to return generation.\n\n### How It Behaves\nInvestment horizons are multi-decade.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Total assets under management\n- Allocation to alternatives\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nFunds pursue direct investments and strategic stakes.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Strategic infrastructure investments\n- Diversification from commodity dependence\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Portfolio Agent**: Incorporates long-term horizon and geopolitical constraints.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nSovereign wealth funds shape global capital flows and strategic industries.\n\n## Related Topics\n- pension_funds.md\n"
