    "route": "/education/macro/global_liquidity",
    "file": "content/education/macro/global_liquidity.md",
    "content": "# Global Liquidity\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nGlobal liquidity is the total availability of money and credit worldwide.\n\n### Origin\nThe concept gained prominence after 2008 when central bank balance sheets became the dominant source.\n\n### Why It Matters\nGlobal liquidity drives risk asset prices and volatility.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nLiquidity is supplied by central banks, commercial banks, and shadow banking.\n\n### How It Behaves\nRising liquidity supports risk-on environments.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Global central bank balance sheets\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nInstitutions increase risk during liquidity expansion.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Liquidity-driven asset allocation\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Macro Agent**: Synthesizes liquidity indicators.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nGlobal liquidity is the master variable of market regimes.\n\n## Related Topics\n- quantitative_easing.md\n"
