    "route": "/education/macro/interest_rates",
    "file": "content/education/macro/interest_rates.md",
    "content": "# Interest Rates\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nInterest rates are the cost of borrowing money or the return on lending.\n\n### Origin\nCentral banks set policy rates as the primary monetary policy tool.\n\n### Why It Matters\nInterest rates are the most important price in the economy.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nPolicy rates influence the entire yield curve and asset valuations.\n\n### How It Behaves\nRate changes transmit through borrowing costs, asset prices, and currency values.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Policy rate and dot plot\n- Yield curve shape\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nInstitutions position portfolios according to expected rate paths.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Rate path forecasting\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Macro Agent**: Models central bank reaction functions.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nInterest rates are the master variable of monetary policy transmission.\n\n## Related Topics\n- monetary_policy.md\n"
