    "file": "content/education/macro/monetary_policy.md",
    "content": "# Monetary Policy\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nMonetary policy is the management of money supply and interest rates by central banks.\n\n### Origin\nModern central banking began with the Federal Reserve in 1913.\n\n### Why It Matters\nMonetary policy is the primary tool for managing inflation and growth.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nTools include policy rates, forward guidance, and quantitative easing.\n\n### How It Behaves\nPolicy is most effective when inflation expectations are anchored.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Policy rate and dot plot\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nInstitutions position according to expected policy paths.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Rate path forecasting\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Macro Agent**: Models central bank reaction functions.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nMonetary policy is the central mechanism of economic management.\n\n## Related Topics\n- interest_rates.md\n"
