    "file": "content/education/macro/treasury_markets.md",
    "content": "# Treasury Markets\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nTreasury markets are the markets for government debt securities issued by sovereigns.\n\n### Origin\nU.S. Treasuries became the global benchmark after World War II.\n\n### Why It Matters\nTreasuries are the risk-free benchmark for all financial pricing.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nTreasuries serve as collateral, safe-haven assets, and monetary policy transmission tools.\n\n### How It Behaves\nTreasury yields reflect growth, inflation, and policy expectations.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Yield curve shape\n- Term premium\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nCentral banks and institutions manage massive Treasury portfolios.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Duration hedging\n- Safe-haven positioning\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Macro Agent**: Interprets Treasury signals as recession indicators.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nTreasury markets are the foundation of global financial pricing.\n\n## Related Topics\n- fixed_income.md\n"
