    "title": "Liquidity Risk",
    "category": "risk_management",
    "slug": "liquidity_risk",
    "route": "/education/risk_management/liquidity_risk",
    "file": "content/education/risk_management/liquidity_risk.md",
    "content": "# Liquidity Risk\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nLiquidity risk is the risk that an asset cannot be sold quickly at a fair price.\n\n### Origin\nLiquidity risk became central after 2008 and 2020 crises.\n\n### Why It Matters\nLiquidity risk can turn solvent institutions illiquid.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nLiquidity risk includes market liquidity and funding liquidity.\n\n### How It Behaves\nLiquidity evaporates during stress, creating feedback loops.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Bid-ask spreads\n- Market depth\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nInstitutions maintain liquidity buffers and stress-test funding needs.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Liquidity coverage ratio management\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Liquidity Agent**: Monitors real-time liquidity stress.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nLiquidity risk is the most dangerous risk because it appears suddenly.\n\n## Related Topics\n- liquidity_crisis.md\n"
