    "slug": "portfolio_hedging",
    "route": "/education/risk_management/portfolio_hedging",
    "file": "content/education/risk_management/portfolio_hedging.md",
    "content": "# Portfolio Hedging\n\n## Beginner Level\n\n### What Is It?\nPortfolio hedging uses derivatives to reduce adverse price risk.\n\n### Origin\nStandard after option pricing models in the 1970s.\n\n### Why It Matters\nHedging allows maintenance of core exposures while limiting downside.\n\n## Intermediate Level\n\n### Market Mechanics\nCommon tools include index futures and options.\n\n### How It Behaves\nHedges reduce volatility but can cap upside.\n\n### Key Data to Watch\n- Hedge ratio effectiveness\n\n## Advanced Level\n\n### Institutional Behavior\nInstitutions run dynamic hedging programs.\n\n### Professional Use Cases\n- Equity tail-risk hedging\n\n### AI Interpretation in Systems Like Arkhe\n- **Risk Agent**: Optimizes hedge ratios.\n\n### Key Takeaways\nPortfolio hedging balances protection with cost.\n\n## Related Topics\n- tail_risk.md\n"
